<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-13T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-13T20:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/5–1446: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">O’Sullivan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-14T08:00:00+07:00">May 14, 1946—8
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 15—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>14. Chinese have officially informed French that withdrawal offers [<hi rend="italic">orders?</hi>] have been recd. French state that
                            according to information given them Chinese withdrawal will commence May
                            15 and will be completed by June 10. French also state their forces were
                            scheduled to enter Luang Prabang yesterday noon. French column entering
                            that city was reinforced during last few days with paratroopers.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed><hi rend="smallcaps">O’Sullivan</hi></signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>